content:
You can score predictions on multiple records at a time. For example, use bulk scoring to refresh all prediction scores after you deploy an updated model.

To view a model:

Click the Scoring tab.
Click Enable.
Select the scope of the records you want to score:
  - Score all ObjectName records
  - Score any ObjectName records that haven't reached a terminal state
  - Score a subset of ObjectName records

Select a subset of records (segment). Specify one or more filter conditions for the records you want score.

Filter expressions are case-sensitive. The value you specify must be an exact match.

Click Start Scoring.
To verify that you want to proceed, click Continue.

Model Manager creates a new scoring job and displays scoring progress. When finished, Model Manager displays the results of the scoring job.

The scoring job displays:
  - Created Date: Date when the scoring job was created
  - Created By: User who created the scoring job
  - Status: Status of the scoring job
  - Total Records Selected: Number of records selected for scoring
  - Scored Successfully: Number of records that were scored successfully
  - With Errors: Number of records with scoring errors

If the daily predictions limit is reached in your org, active scoring jobs are paused, then resumed the next day.

To manage scoring jobs:
  - Click Cancel to cancel a scoring job in progress
  - Click Run Again to run a scoring job again
  - Click Delete to delete a scoring job
title: Bulk Scoring with Salesforce Einstein Discovery
